<br>
I've found that of a typical group of 5 or 6, four of us will actually do a decent job. We figure out each others fighting styles and get into a groove in just a few fights. But there is always that 1 (sometimes 2) person(s) who just DON'T GET IT. <br>
<br>
For that person here is some advice:<br>
<br>
1.) Rangers have snare, use it! One of my biggest peeves is when fighting in a dungeon with my cleric healing the group and fight after fight the ranger keeps Rooting the mob instead of snaring. &lt;snarl&gt;<br>
2.) Slowers, don't hit the mob with slow during the pull! And if you do, don't be surprised when the group wipes.<br>
3.) If you are getting hit, and you are not the MT, fix the problem. Chances are it's you. If you don't have the AC/HP to be the MT, don't try.<br>
4.) When there is a Chanter in group, DON'T try to off tank, DON'T root and dot adds, DO use /assist on the MT. DON'T expect the MT to change to your target. If you feel the need to peel a mob off a caster, use taunt, snare / stun (low level with no damage), or some other high agro non damage causing spell.<br>
5.) When on a dungeon crawl, STAY WITH THE GROUP! I don't care if you want to see what's around that bend. Trust me, you won't be pleased when you find out.<br>
<br>
Ok, I feel better now. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~mcjohnson/images/EQ/sig55.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
