<br>
I have a recent example to support this point.  The other night, I hosted a crawl in Crystal Caverns with the goal of simply going to Frostone (?) without levitating and dropping down.  I am a 32nd nec and the rest of the group proper was under 25. (we had supervision)  <br>
<br>
Anyhow, I was curious whether one of my group member's spells would stick to the orcs.  We were still at the top of CC so I walked in a bit, after we had cleared the front orcs, and targetted a random orc.  I told the group mate to /assist me and con my target.  So, he walk ahead to find an orc.  Unfortunately, he got a bit close to the edge of the cavern and fell down to the first ice bridge.  He did not last very long.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, about 10 seconds after his demise, we heard the cries of &quot;Your blood shall flow like the veins of velium in this cavern&quot; (or some other nonesense).  I kept an eye on the entrance and did manage to get out &quot;ZONE!&quot; before the 9 or 10 orcs came rushing us.  Fortunately, only one of our chaperones got dead (the 60 or so cleric made it).  Was seriously the best train I had seen for quite some time.   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/fallenmicaela/tzesig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
