<br>
He's also a bit of a coward. At one time we were all invised and checking on spawns on the fire wing. His invis fell and a monster starts beating him up. SK and warrior were on the monster right away (pulled it off him).  He didnt notice it though (he's probably too frightened) and hit DA, shouts train to zone, and ran to the zone line like a frightened girl, leaving us ( I exodused us 2x already when it looks like 3 or more monsters we're fighting is going to wipe us but I guess he didnt get it).   However, the shaman, after slowing the monster, was able to keep the sk MT alive.<br>
<br>
So we fight our last named (fire mini boss), he let the sk mt died (as usual). Warrior then tanks the named and I was really confused because it took a while for fire named to chew on the warrior's hp but he did NOT toss a single heal. Cleric was thinking he's a paladin and meleeing beside the tank. After the warrior died I got summoned and was being chewed up. I could have exodused the rest of us to safety(its almost instant cast) but I choose not to and hoped that the cleric would die with us (hehe).<br>
<br>
He's a smart cleric though. His pathetic DPS and I-wont-heal-anybody attitude put him at the bottom of the aggro list. The ranger, who probably became MT after I died, noticed that he's healing the MONSTER (he's probably thinking that healing monsters lowers aggro&gt;).  The end result....we all popped naked at our bind point except for him who probably hit his DA, pushed his train shout hotbutton, and ran as fast as his chicken ass can take him to kiss the BOT zone out stone.  I got a little angry after that and asked him (in group say) why he didnt heal the tank. He said something like healing is not an easy job and yelled at me to get off his back. He's prolly right, I know nothing about clerics except to cast CH if tank at 50% and mob slowed, or cast fast heal at 50-60% (if monster is unslowed) and cast CH.<br>
<br>
In the end, I felt bad about not exodusing us. I underestimated the cleric's survival instincts. <br>
He's not that bad though. He zoned back in and rezzed all of us except the SK. I dont know what went on between them. Prolly a mild misunderstanding. I guess he felt that the SK has exceeded his rez quota for the day.  He also stayed with us for the entire 7 hr BOT grind which is a plus (most clerics usually leave the group after 2 hrs or so)<br>
<br>
All in all, he's a bad cleric (I think) but he's the norm I guess because I found 2 other clerics like him :P. Not as bad as *B******, but the same behaviour.  Anyways, a bad cleric is better than no cleric.<br>
